snippet: There are concerns about whether the forces that have driven the market rally — government spending and banner corporate profits — will be sufficient to push it higher.
abstract: Dow Jones industrial average surges past the nominal high it reached in 2007 to all-time high of 14,253.77 points; market measure has more than doubled since hitting low in March 2009; concerns remain about whether forces that have driven the market rally--government spending and banner corporate profits--will be sufficient to push it higher.

byline.contributor: Susanne Craig, Nathaniel Popper and Michael J. de la Merced contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: There are concerns about whether the forces that have driven the market rally — government spending and banner corporate profits — will be sufficient to push it higher.

headline.seo: Cheers Are Few as Dow Jones Average Hits Milestone
headline.main: As Fears Recede, Dow Industrials Hit a Milestone
headline.print_headline: As Fears Recede, Dow Industrials Hit a Milestone
